pages:9.0:8:
{"text":"Because of the amount of exploration in this modpack, the file size of world files can get quite large.
To make you backups smaller and faster, you can use the AromaBackup config (found in config > aroma1997 > aromabackup.cfg).
If you set
useWhitelist = true
you can specify a list of dimensions that will be backed up, and the rest will be ignored, keeping files smaller, and faster to generate.
SEE NEXT PAGE"}
pages:9.1:8: {"text":"The whitelist field will let you select the list of dimensions to backup.\nIf no changes are made, and the useWhitelist flag is toggled, the backup will include the Overworld, the Nether, the End, and the Void (0, -1, 1, 43)."}
